Description: The Production Room is a full service graphic design studio specializing in website design and hosting.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: The Production Room is a full service graphic design studio specializing in website design and hosting. Other services include print media design, multi media presentations, prepress and print brokering. Their goal was to provide full-color printing and design services using a PC platform. Many laughed and said it couldn't be done, they would need a Macintosh! It can't be done? Well, this made it an even sweeter challenge. After all, their specialty has always been to do what others say can not be done. So they offered a wide range of services, designed and printed many full color jobs on their PC’s and watched as the PC slowly infiltrated the design world. They took on many "odd projects" and never said "no, they can't". Eventually they did break down and add a Macintosh to their network of computers and expanded their services to include service bureau output that would accommodate both PC and Mac users. Now with the new millennium upon us and the boom of the digital age their focus is, of course, the Internet. They offer a wide range of digital services including web site design and hosting, digital photography/video and of course, graphic design. They still take on almost any job a client throws at us, and if they can't do it (which isn't often) they will direct the client to the best source for the job. They have been traditionally trained, but they’re technology driven.

Description: EarGames is an independent game studio founded in 2013 by 26 year game veteran Brian Schmidt.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: EarGames was founded in 2012 with a vision of making games where sound, not visuals drive the gameplay. After decades in the industry, including 10 years as audio architect for the Xbox™ and Xbox 360™, Brian created EarGames with a desire to create fast-paced, arcade-style sound-based gameplay for mobile devices and tablets. Brian Schmidt has been creating sound, music and sound technology for games since 1987, when he was hired as a composer and programmer for pinball machines at Williams Electronic Games. Since then, he has made a name for himself as one of the game industry’s leading audio technologists and composers, having personally composed music for over 130 arcade and console games.  During the design of the Xbox, Brian was the driving force behind bringing interactive Dolby Digital™ Surround Sound to console gaming, allowing game action to be heard outside the confines of the game screen and envelope the player. It is that vision that drives EarGames’ titles—that sound can be a primary driver of action-based gameplay, focusing on the use of HRTF 3D Sound technology.
